The paper presents a machine learning approach to detecting arousals in polysomnographic recordings, which involves signal processing and sequence learning using recurrent neural networks. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Among these, cs.LG and cs.NE are the most likely categories, as they are directly related to the machine learning and neural network aspects of the paper. However, the paper also involves signal processing and feature extraction, which could make cs.CV a relevant category as well. Finally, the use of recurrent neural networks suggests a temporal aspect to the analysis, which could make cs.SI a possible category as well.
